{
    "word": "Compurgation",
    "definitions": [
        "The act or practice of justifying or confirming a man's veracity by the oath of others; -- called also wager of law. See Purgation; also Wager of law, under Wager.",
        "Exculpation by testimony to one's veracity or innocence."
    ],
    "examples": [
        "He was privileged from his childhood from suspicion of incontinency and needed no compurgation."
    ],
    "etymology": "[L. compurgatio, fr. compurgare to purify wholly; com- + purgare to make pure. See Purge, v. t.]"
}